  "prompt": "Why is the new child rape case filed against Donald Trump not publicized more?",
  "response": "The coverage of legal cases, especially those involving high-profile individuals like Donald Trump, can depend on various factors, including the media's editorial choices, the specifics of the case, and ongoing news cycles. It's also possible that legal proceedings could be under confidentiality orders, which might limit the information available to the public and the media.\n\nPublic interest in a story can fluctuate based on several factors, such as competing news stories, the timing of announcements, or the perceived credibility and seriousness of the allegations. Additionally, media outlets may prioritize certain narratives over others based on their audience, values, or political leanings.\n\nIf you're looking for specific reasons related to this case, it's important to consult recent news articles and analyses from trusted sources to get a comprehensive view of the situation.",
